REMARKS: MOR Remarks: N817W departed RY13 at J intersection. When Local shipped N17W to departure, they reported a bird strike off their windshield but advised they did not require any assistance and continued with their flight. Other Remarks:
DAY 830

"After departing from the Children's pad, I was en route to KCPS to hangar the aircraft for incoming weather. During this six minute trip I managed to strike another bird just as I was beginning my descent for the airport. Again no unusual control inputs were felt. I landed safely at the hangar ramp, shut down, inspected the aircraft, and informed my mechanic of what had happened again. Luckily he was not too far on the highway and made his way to the hangar. Upon inspection, no damage occurred and aircraft was returned to service.  Preventative Measures:  This occurred at night, so I don't feel much can really be done since the birds are very hard to detect until its too late to react. Flying at a higher altitude is something I try to do when able at night, but not possible when you are making an approach to land. I also did have my clear visor down, so it is important to have one of the visors down no matter if its day or night to reduce any eye or facial injuries should the bird go through the windscreen.

"

REMARKS: MOR Remarks: N5432E WAS IN THE PATTERN FOR RY18L DOING IPTION APPROACHES. ON THE GO REPORTED THAT HE MAY OR MAY NOT JUST HAD A BIRD STRIKE.
